# Cursor Rule: Analytics Event ID and Name Guidelines

This rule defines how to name analytics data attributes used by the site-wide auto button tracker.

## Scope
- Applies to any interactive element that should be tracked by `AutoButtonTracking`.
- Use these attributes on the element that carries `data-slot="button"` (our `Button` component or its `asChild` anchor).

## Attributes
- `data-analytics-id`: Stable, machine-friendly ID
- `data-analytics-name`: Human-readable label
- `data-analytics-context`: Small JSON string with structured params

## ID Guidelines (`data-analytics-id`)
- Format: lowercase snake_case
- Pattern: `[surface]_[action][_variant][_qualifiers]`
- Allowed chars: `[a-z0-9_]`; keep ≤ 64 chars
- Must be stable across copy changes; do not include display text

### Common surfaces
- `nav_desktop`, `nav_mobile`
- `home_hero`, `home_call_to_action`
- `case_studies_hero`, `case_studies_call_to_action`, `case_study_call_to_action`
- `pricing_cta_{plan_key}_{billing}`

### Common actions
- `demo`, `signup`, `contact_sales`, `learn_more`

### Dynamics
- Pricing: `pricing_cta_{plan_key}_{billing}`
  - `plan_key`: stable snake_case key (e.g., `professional_plus`)
  - `billing`: `annual` | `monthly` | `custom`
- A/B variants: append `_v{n}` or `_variant_{key}`
- Locale: append `_en`, `_es` if needed

## Name Guidelines (`data-analytics-name`)
- Format: `{Action Label} (Surface Label)`
- Human-friendly and short; do not encode technical params (put in context)
- Examples:
  - `Get Demo (Nav)` / `Get Demo (Nav Mobile)`
  - `Get Demo (Home Hero)` / `Get Demo (Home CTA)`
  - `Get Demo (Case Studies Hero)` / `Get Demo (Case Studies CTA)`
  - `Get Demo (Case Study CTA)`
  - Pricing: `{Plan Name} (Pricing)` (e.g., `Professional (Pricing)`)

## Context Guidelines (`data-analytics-context`)
- JSON string; concise and structured
- Common fields:
  - `source`: stable surface key (e.g., `pricing`, `home_hero`)
  - `section`: semantic area (e.g., `hero`, `call-to-action`)
  - `plan`: snake_case plan key for pricing
  - `billing`: `annual` | `monthly` | `custom`
  - Optional: `variant`, `ab_test`, `ab_group`, `locale`
- Example:
```json
{"source":"pricing","section":"pricing","plan":"professional","billing":"annual"}
```

## Do / Don’t
- Do keep IDs immutable across copy tweaks
- Do keep Names readable; parameters live in `data-analytics-context`
- Don’t include spaces/punctuation or copy text in IDs
- Don’t duplicate parameters in the Name if they’re already in Context

## Implementation Notes
- Our auto-tracker reads:
  - `data-analytics-id` → `button_id`
  - `data-analytics-name` → event label
  - `data-analytics-context` (JSON) → merged into event context
- Buttons should render with `data-slot="button"` (handled by our `Button` component)


